The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Convergys open to buyouts 

 G. S. RADHAKRISHNA

 Hyderabad, Feb. 9: Convergys Corporation plans to expand its operations and acquire more companies in India.

 ?We will invest millions of dollars to strengthen our infrastructure and train manpower for our contact centre, BPO and software development operations in India,? said Larry S. Schwart, executive vice-president (global operations), information management group. 

 He has inaugurated the 85,000-sq-ft, IT campus-cum-software development centre of the company at the Hitech City. Convergys has already inducted 600 employees in Hyderabad for software and product development.

 ?The second phase of expansion is expected to be completed by April, whereby we will double the size of our manpower in Hyderabad,? Schwart said. 

 He said the Hyderabad IT campus ? the eighth facility of the company in India ? will become a centre of excellence and also cater to the Asia-Pacific operations of the group.

 Convergys had opted for India due to the development in the infrastructure and connectivity sectors. 




